text: Aldershot Town Football Club is a professional association football club in Aldershot, Hampshire, England. The team competes in the National League. It is the fifth tier of the English football league system. The club was founded in the spring of 1992. They won the First Division title in 1997–98 and the Premier Division in 2002–03 to gain a place in the Conference. They spent five seasons in League Two, reaching the play-offs in 2010. They reached the National League play-offs in 2017 and 2018. ==References== Category:English football clubs
